Set Up

In this lab, we will perform pseudo-experiment data analysis. We will be using our optimized event selection to hunt for our signal by using one of the pseudo-experiment dataset. For each problem, we will choose one of the observed data from our specific pT sample to perform the analysis.

In [178]:
# returns an arr with values greater than a and b and its significance
def cut(a,b,higgs,qcd):
    # filter out values outside of a and b
    higgs_cut = higgs[higgs>a]
    higgs_cut = higgs_cut[higgs_cut<b]
    
    qcd_cut = qcd[qcd>a]
    qcd_cut = qcd_cut[qcd_cut<b]
    
    # gets cut version of array and significance
    higgs_n = 100*len(higgs_cut)/len(higgs)
    qcd_n = 20000*len(qcd_cut)/len(qcd)
    
    sig = abs(stats.norm.ppf(1-stats.poisson.cdf(higgs_n+qcd_n,qcd_n)))
    print(f"Significance for Range {a}-{b}:", sig)
    return higgs_cut, qcd_cut, sig

# returns arr with optimal mass cut
def opt_cut(higgs,qcd):
    # filter out values outside of optimal mass cut
    higgs_cut = higgs[higgs_data.mass>124]
    higgs_cut = higgs_cut[higgs_data.mass<128]
    
    qcd_cut = qcd[qcd_data.mass>124]
    qcd_cut = qcd_cut[qcd_data.mass<128]

    return higgs_cut, qcd_cut

fig, ax = plt.subplots(14, 2)
fig.set_size_inches(20,140)
features = ['pt','eta','phi','mass','ee2','ee3','d2', \
            'angularity','t1','t2','t3','t21','t32','KtDeltaR']

for i in range(14):
    feature = features[i]
    ax[i,0].set_title(f"Expected Signal for {feature}", fontsize=20)
    ax[i,0].set_xlabel(feature, fontsize=18)
    ax[i,0].set_ylabel('Counts', fontsize=18)
    ax[i,0].hist(higgs_data[feature],500,alpha=0.5,label='Higgs Data')
    n, bins, rects = ax[i,0].hist(high_lumi[feature],500,alpha=0.5,label='High Luminosity')
    for r in rects: 
        factor = len(high_lumi[feature])/len(higgs_data[feature])
        r.set_height(r.get_height()/factor)
    ax[i,0].legend(loc='upper right')
    
    ax[i,1].set_title(f"Expected Background for {feature}", fontsize=20)
    ax[i,1].set_xlabel(feature, fontsize=18)
    ax[i,1].set_ylabel('Counts', fontsize=18)
    ax[i,1].hist(qcd_data[feature],500,alpha=0.5,label='QCD Background')
    n, bins, rects = ax[i,1].hist(high_lumi[feature],500,alpha=0.5,label='High Luminosity')
    for r in rects: 
        factor = len(high_lumi[feature])/len(qcd_data[feature])
        r.set_height(r.get_height()/factor)
    ax[i,1].legend(loc='upper right')

Section 1c

Here, we will evaluate observed significance and compare our results to expectation. Here, we see the significance of the observed data and the expected data are very different. For a majority of the features, we have a significance of infinity in the observed data. The features with a non-infinity value, only the t3 feature is somewhat similar to the expected. This is most likely because of the length of the cut background data being too small which could affect the significance.
